The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Sunday, April 22, 2007

 Tea time 

 Dont miss Tea Festival, an exhibition of brews followed by a tea tasting session, at Urban Courtyard, Swabhumi, 4 pm.

 eye on Art 

 Browse through drawings and paintings of The Blue Boy by Snehangshu Shekhar Dasat Academy of Fine Arts, 3 pm to 8 pm. 

 The beaches of Digha on canvas in Inspiration, a show by several artists, at Artists Circle, 2 pm to 7 pm. 

 Drop in to a painting exhibition by Spectrum Artists Circle at Chitrakoot Art Gallery, 3 pm to 8 pm. 

 On stage 

 Enjoy an evening of song and dance by Keya Chanda and troupe at Gyan Manch, 6.15 pm.

 isten to an interaction on the occasion of Bangla Sangeet Mela at Bangla Academy Sabhaghar, 6.30 pm. 

 Take part in a training programme on creative dance/movement therapy by Tripura Kashyap at Eastern Zonal Cultural Centre, 11 am to 5 pm. 

 Jewellery show

 Check out a semi-precious jewellery collection by Art Karat at Genesis Art Gallery, 11 am to 8 pm.

 Book launch 

 Be there at the launch of It Happened in India by Kishore Biyani at GD Birla Sabhaghar, 5.15 pm.




